Date:  0/0/1868
Source:  Contributions to NZ Botany
Author:  LiNDSAY
Vol / Page:  68
Edition:
Quote:  <i>V[eronica] Salicifolia</i>, Forst. ... in allusion to its frequent habit and habitat - on the banks of streams - it is locally known as the New Zealand `Willow', (Buchanan.) The Otago settlers also call it `Korimuka', (Martin,) - `Korumeek,' (Hector,) - properly spelled `Koromiko' - a term also applied to <i>V. parviflora</i>, Vahl. ... and perhaps in general, to all <i>shrubby</i>species of the genus.
Notes:

